This is a list of international presidential trips made by George H.W. Bush, the 41th president of the United States. George H. W. Bush made 26 international trips to 58 different countries on six continents—Africa, Asia, Australia, Europe, North America, and South America—during his presidency, which began on January 20, 1989 and ended on January 20, 1993.
The number of visits per country where he travelled are:
One visit to Argentina, Australia, Chile, China, Colombia, Costa Rica, Czechoslovakia, Egypt, Greece, Hungary, Malta, Martinique, Mexico, Panama, Russia, Saint Martin, Singapore, Somalia, Soviet Union, Spain, Switzerland, Turkey, Uruguay, and Venezuela
Two visits to Belgium, Bermuda, Brazil, Finland, Italy, Japan, Netherlands, Poland, Saudi Arabia, South Korea, and Vatican City
Three visits to Germany (including one to West Germany), and the United Kingdom
Four visits to Canada, and France
